            "answer_text": "6,500,000,000 According to American system, a billion is a thousand times a  million. That is, when we want to convert a number expressed in billions, we should multiply it by 10^9 (10 raised to the power of 9). 1 million = 10^6 1 thousand= 10^3 Therefore, a billion is 10^6 * 10^3 which is 10^9. So, now multiply the number by 10^9. 6.5 * 10^12 = 6,500,000,000  ",
